# AutoForge Overview

AutoForge is an AI-native software engineering platform that orchestrates multiple specialized agents through a serial pipeline to design, implement, and verify software projects. It combines a chat-first interface, a structured specification system, and a relay pipeline that routes tasks between profession-specific agents.

## Technology Stack

### Backend

| Technology | Version | Source | Purpose |
|------------|---------|--------|---------|
| **Rust** | 1.80+ | `Cargo.toml` | Systems programming, memory safety |
| **Axum** | 0.8 | `Cargo.toml` | Web framework (REST + WebSocket + SSE) |
| **Tokio** | 1.x | `Cargo.toml` | Async runtime |
| **Reqwest** | 0.12 | `Cargo.toml` | HTTP client for LLM APIs |
| **Serde** | 1.x | `Cargo.toml` | Serialization |
| **Tower-HTTP** | 0.6 | `Cargo.toml` | CORS, static file serving |
| **Tracing** | 0.1 | `Cargo.toml` | Observability |
| **UUID** | 1.x | `Cargo.toml` | Session identifiers |

### Frontend

| Technology | Version | Source | Purpose |
|------------|---------|--------|---------|
| **Vue 3** | 3.5+ | `package.json` | UI framework (Composition API) |
| **Vite** | 6.x | `package.json` | Build tool + dev server |
| **TypeScript** | 5.8+ | `package.json` | Type safety |
| **TipTap** | 3.23+ | `package.json` | ProseMirror-based block editor |
| **Mermaid** | 11.15+ | `package.json` | Diagram rendering in specs |
| **Markstream** | 0.0.14-beta.8 | `package.json` | Streaming Markdown renderer |

### AI Providers

| Provider | Models | Configuration |
|----------|--------|---------------|
| **Anthropic** | Claude 3.5 Opus / Sonnet / Haiku | `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` env or `~/.claude/settings.json` |
| **OpenAI** | GPT-4o | `OPENAI_API_KEY` env |
| **Local** | Ollama / custom | Local URL in API Sources config |

## System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph UI["User Interface"]
        Chat[Chat]
        SpecsView[Specs]
        WikiView[Wiki]
        RelayPanel[Relay Pipeline]
    end

    subgraph Orchestrator["Agent Orchestrator"]
        Assistant[Assistant<br/>Intake]
        Advisor[Advisor<br/>Discovery]
        Architect[Architect<br/>Design]
        Planner[Planner<br/>Plan]
        Coder[Coder<br/>Code]
        Tester[Tester<br/>Verify]
        Reviewer[Reviewer<br/>Validation]
        Documenter[Documenter<br/>Report]
    end

    subgraph Core["Core Services"]
        Provider[Provider<br/>LLM SSE]
        Tools[Tools<br/>FS / Shell]
        ProjectMgr[Project<br/>Workspace]
        Checkpoint[Checkpoint<br/>Durability]
        SpecsStore[Specs Store<br/>AD / AT]
    end

    UI --> Orchestrator
    Orchestrator --> Core
```

## Core Concepts

| Concept | Definition | Lives In |
|---------|------------|----------|
| **Soul** | Markdown personality definition for an agent (values, style, rituals) | `agent-config` |
| **Profession** | Capability contract: owned specs, readable specs, allowed tools, handoff targets | `agent-config` |
| **Relay** | Serial agent pipeline with baton-passing handoff documents | `relay` |
| **Gate** | Human-in-the-loop approval point (GSD auto-approve vs Check explicit) | `relay` / `chat` |
| **Handoff** | Compressed context document passed between agents (~5× token savings) | `relay` |
| **Spec** | Structured decision record in `.ad` format (Goals → Architecture → Designs → Plans → Tests → Reviews → Reports) | `specs` |
| **Checkpoint** | JSON + git snapshot for crash recovery without chat history | `runtime` |
| **Errand** | Fire-and-forget research task in isolated context | `errand` |

## Core Flows

Five execution flows span multiple modules. See [flows.ad](flows.ad) for full sequence diagrams and step-by-step breakdowns.

| Flow | Entry | Exit | Key Modules |
|------|-------|------|-------------|
| **Forge Chat Loop** | User sends message | SSE delivers response | chat, provider, runtime, relay |
| **Relay Pipeline** | FlowSpec loaded | Completed / Failed / Paused | relay, provider, runtime, specs |
| **Agent Turn** | Agent spawned with profession | Handoff document returned | agent-config, provider, runtime |
| **Spec Lifecycle** | Agent reads/writes spec | Persisted to `.ad` with derived statuses | specs, forge |
| **Gate Approval** | Step has `gate: true` | User approves/rejects | relay, chat, ui-system |

